text: Paige van der Westhuizen (born 23 April 2003) is a Zimbabwean swimmer. She represented Zimbabwe at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships held in Gwangju, South Korea. She competed in the women's 100 metre freestyle and women's 200 metre freestyle events. In both events she did not advance to compete in the semi-finals. ==References== Category:2003 births Category:Living people Category:Zimbabwean female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Female freestyle swimmers
